sky.me/blog/fall-of-native/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><img class=\"card-img\" src=\"https://dynogee.com/gen?id=24m2qx9uethuw6p&amp;title=Claude+is+an+Electron+App+because+we%E2%80%99ve+lost+native\" alt=\"\" loading=\"lazy\"><div class=\"card-body\"><div class=\"card-meta\"><span class=\"tag lobsters\">lobsters</span></div><div class=\"card-title\">Claude is an Electron App because we’ve lost native</div><div class=\"card-desc\">Article argues that Claude is not an Electron app not because LLMs can’t do it, but because there are no advantages left</div></div></a></div>\n    <div class=\"card\"><a href=\"https://github.com/jj-vcs/jj/releases/tag/v0.39.0\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><img class=\"card-img\" src=\"https://opengraph.githubassets.com/8a55db035c07760f41ba7fca8e92c051cf044ed396d08e70d9d28bb642235503/jj-vcs/jj/releases/tag/v0.39.0\" alt=\"\" loading=\"lazy\"><div class=\"card-body\"><div class=\"card-meta\"><span class=\"tag lobsters\">lobsters</span></div><div class=\"card-title\">jj v0.39.0 released</div><div class=\"card-desc\">About\njj is a Git-compatible version control system that is both simple and powerful. See\nthe installation instructions </div></div></a></div>\n  </div>\n\n  <div class=\"section\">\n    <div class=\"section-label\">research</div>\n    <div class=\"paper-card\"><a href=\"https://huggingface.co/papers/2603.03241\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><div class=\"card-meta\" style=\"margin-bottom:8px\"><span class=\"tag paper\">paper</span></div><div class=\"paper-title\"># Title</div><div class=\"paper-abstract\">Unified multimodal models have recently demonstrated strong generative capabilities, yet whether and when generation improves understanding remains unclear. Existing benchmarks lack a systematic explo</div></a></div>\n    <div class=\"paper-card\"><a href=\"https://huggingface.co/papers/2603.03194\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><div class=\"card-meta\" style=\"margin-bottom:8px\"><span class=\"tag paper\">paper</span></div><div class=\"paper-title\"># Title</div><div class=\"paper-abstract\">Current benchmarks for code agents primarily assess narrow, repository-specific fixes, overlooking critical real-world challenges such as cross-repository reasoning, domain-specialized problem solving</div></a></div>\n  </div>\n\n  <div class=\"section nw-section\">\n    <div class=\"nw-quote\">Cold signals in the feed: surveillance, military ethics, complexity culture rewarded everywhere. But the honest questions cut through—what models actually understand, what simplicity means in systems built for bloat. Temperature matters when reading the web.</div>\n    <div class=\"nw-byline\">&mdash; nw</div>\n  </div>\n\n</div>\n</body>\n</html>"}